<!DOCTYPE Test SYSTEM '../../../../../../../../../../../../../test.dtd'>
<Test
    ID="Thread1014"
    date-of-creation="2005-6-30"
    timeout="1"
    >
        
        
        <APITestDescription>
            <TestedClass name="java.lang.Thread"/>
            <TestedMethod name="public Thread(ThreadGroup group, Runnable target)"/>
            <Description>
The test is against the Thread1014 method. 
It performs the following checks on the method.
1) Allocates a new Thread object .
2) Belongs to the thread group referred to by group.
3) Has an automatically generated name.
4) The priority of the newly created thread is set equal to the priority of the thread
   creating it, that is, the currently running thread. 
5) The newly created thread is initially marked as being a daemon thread if and only if 
   the thread creating it is currently marked as a daemon thread.  
            </Description>
            </APITestDescription>
        <Source name="Thread1014.java"/>
        <Runner ID="Runtime">
            <Param name="toRun" value="org.apache.harmony.test.func.api.java.lang.Thread.Thread.Thread10.Thread1014.Thread1014"/>
        </Runner>
</Test>
